headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 22 points off the bench, Darius Garland had 21 points and nine assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers routed the Philadelphia 76ers 113-85 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Caris LeVert scores 22 points, Cavaliers rout 76ers 113-85

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 30 points and 14 assists and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a three-game losing streak with a 125-108 win over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Hawks stop 3-game skid with 125-108 win over Magic

headlines.description: — Camera phones throughout Boston's TD Garden were fixed on the seats adjacent the Celtics' bench as the Prince and...
headlines.shortLinkText: Royal night: Tatum scores 49, Celtics hold off Heat 134-121

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 39 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Washington Wizards 113-107 on Wednesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 39 points, Nets beat Wizards 113-107

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 37 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists, then Grayson Allen made the tiebreaking 3-pointer with 30 seconds left after his superstar teammate fouled out to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 109-103 victory over the New York...
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen, Bucks hang on after Giannis fouls out to edge Knicks

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 29 points, five steals and three blocks to lead Minnesota to a 109-101 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night in the first game of an extended absence for injured Timberwolves star Karl-Anthony Towns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards sparks Towns-less T-wolves, 109-101 over Grizzlies

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 33 points, four steals and two blocks, and Trey Murphy added six 3-pointers and 26 points as the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Toronto Raptors 126-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 33, powers Pelicans past Raptors 126-108

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Oklahoma City didn't have star Shai Gilgeous-Alexander against San Antoni. Jalen Williams' spot-on imitation was good enough.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams scores 27 points, Thunder push Spurs' skid to 9

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 26 points, Nikola Jokic had 10 of his 12 assists in the first half and the Denver Nuggets cruised past the Houston Rockets 120-100 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic guide Nuggets to 120-100 rout of Rockets

headlines.description: — Devin Booker made the Chicago Bulls pay for some mediocre defense with a couple early mid-range jumpers. Then he made a few more. And a few more.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 51 points in 3 quarters, Suns rout Bulls

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson had a season-high 33 points and five assists, and the Utah Jazz snapped a five-game losing streak with a 125-112 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 33, Jazz beat Clippers to snap 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes and Malik Monk each scored 22 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the Indiana Pacers 137-114 on Wednesday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk and Barnes score 22 each, Kings beat Pacers

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 31 points, eight assists and seven rebounds, Austin Reaves added a season-high 22 points and the Los Angeles Lakers rebounded from a heartbreaking loss with a 128-109 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron gets 31 in Lakers' 128-109 rout of Dame-less Blazers
